  • java.lang.Object
    • dk.sdu.mmmi.cfei.dataframes.TimeSeries<T>

    public class TimeSeries<T extends Number>
extends Object
implements Iterable<Reading<T>>
    A time series of values. A time series is a sequence of pairs: a datetime and a value.

      • setContiguous

        public void setContiguous(TimeSeries<T> that)
        Set the values from a given time series. For instance, given a first time series: 
         
 first =
     2015-01-05 12:55 | 24.6
     2015-01-05 12:59 | 28.7
     2015-01-05 15:08 | 26.3
     2015-01-05 15:28 | 13.8
     2015-01-05 17:08 | 27.4
        and a second time series: 
         
 second =
     2015-01-05 15:08 | 999.0
     2015-01-05 15:28 | 666.6
        calling 
         
 first.set(second);
        will set the values of first to 
         
 first =
     2015-01-05 12:55 | 24.6
     2015-01-05 12:59 | 28.7
     2015-01-05 15:08 | 999.0
     2015-01-05 15:28 | 666.6
     2015-01-05 17:08 | 27.4
        Note that the other time series must be contained in this time series and that the other time series must not have any hole. If there are holes, use set(TimeSeries).
        Parameters:
        that - The other time series.

      • set

        public void set(TimeSeries<T> that,
                boolean skipNaNs)
        Set the values from a given time series. For instance, given a first time series: 
         
 first =
     2015-01-05 12:55 | 24.6
     2015-01-05 12:59 | 28.7
     2015-01-05 15:08 | 26.3
     2015-01-05 15:28 | 13.8
     2015-01-05 17:08 | 27.4
        and a second time series: 
         
 second =
     2015-01-05 15:08 | 999.0
     2015-01-05 15:28 | 666.6
        calling 
         
 first.set(second);
        will set the values of first to 
         
 first =
     2015-01-05 12:55 | 24.6
     2015-01-05 12:59 | 28.7
     2015-01-05 15:08 | 999.0
     2015-01-05 15:28 | 666.6
     2015-01-05 17:08 | 27.4
        Note that the other time series must be contained in this time series.
        Parameters:
        that - The other time series.
        skipNaNs - Skip NaN values.
